{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"readonly"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:Q$objc(cs)NSArray","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"NSArray<MLNPolygon *>"},{"kind":"text","text":" * "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"interiorPolygons"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The area occupied by any interior polygons is excluded from the overall shape."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Interior polygons should not overlap. An interior polygon should not have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interior polygons of its own."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If there are no interior polygons, the value of this property is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon\/interiorpolygons"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/interiorPolygons","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"interiorPolygons"}],"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNPolygon(py)interiorPolygons","title":"interiorPolygons","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"interiorPolygons"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The array of polygons nested inside the receiver."}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon/interiorPolygons":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"interiorPolygons","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The array of polygons nested inside the receiver."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/interiorPolygons","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"interiorPolygons"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon\/interiorpolygons"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon":{"role":"symbol","title":"MLNPolygon","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a closed shape consisting of four or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"vertices, specified as "},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the edges that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use a polygon shape to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"building, a lake, or an area you want to highlight.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPolygon","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","title":"MapLibre","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"}}}